  {
    "client_msg_id": "d415f195-8c13-47e0-b808-4c69adce93c6",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Hi Parris. I'm interested in learning more about StoryForj. I work on a team that's still doing a lot of Flash work (yeah, I know). I'm curious what the overlap between Flash and StoryForj is. Do you have tools for drawing artwork? Keyframe animation?",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1568331902.183500",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "gf94d2ed5e18",
      "image_72": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6f94d2ed5e188be9865a531021b0afcd.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0013-72.png",
      "first_name": "Ivan",
      "real_name": "Ivan Reese",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "ivanreese",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1568330809.182600",
    "parent_user_id": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "channel_name": "introduce-yourself",
    "channel_id": "CC2JRGVLK"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "d051eaaf-32a9-456b-8c81-9deb0b907df4",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UC2A2ARPT> ooo that is def surprising and interesting! No keyframe animations or ability to draw artwork unfortunately (yet). We do have some pre-canned animations, and we wouldn't be too far off from letting you build your own animations up from scratch.\n\nAs of right now our interactivity is mostly focused on showing/hiding things, and screen navigation. We allow for branching or linear (scrolling up/down or swiping left/right) screen navigation.\n\nWe may *not* be well suited if you often create characters and do a lot of animation in Flash. Buttttt you have inspired me. Would love to hear more about why your team still uses Flash. Honestly, I kinda miss the Flash days. There's still a level of interactivity we can't pull off right now with our current web tech.",
    "user": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "ts": "1568333018.183700",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "2cbc18c8ae90",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-09-12/760980944038_2cbc18c8ae90630cd996_72.png",
      "first_name": "",
      "real_name": "Parris",
      "display_name": "Parris",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "parris",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "edited": {
      "user": "UMXUZ97LJ",
      "ts": "1568333361.000000"
    },
    "thread_ts": "1568330809.182600",
    "parent_user_id": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "channel_name": "introduce-yourself",
    "channel_id": "CC2JRGVLK"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "f5e77b47-875c-4509-b0c1-5012272459f4",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "We make these interactive simulations: <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AFvFNHWTy5U>\n\nAt this point we only use Flash (now Animate) to draw the artwork, because our artists prefer those drawing tools to Illustrator or Sketch. We export SVGs and add interactivity using some in-house JS frameworks and GUI tools.\n\nI'm surprised that you use Flash as the point of comparison for StoryForj, not least of all because Flash has such a polarized reputation! I see your tool as making content more akin to digital articles rather than the games and animations Flash was known for. Is that just due to the initial focus, with plans to broaden the reach of your tool?",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1568335382.184300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "gf94d2ed5e18",
      "image_72": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/6f94d2ed5e188be9865a531021b0afcd.jpg?s=72&d=https%3A%2F%2Fa.slack-edge.com%2Fdf10d%2Fimg%2Favatars%2Fava_0013-72.png",
      "first_name": "Ivan",
      "real_name": "Ivan Reese",
      "display_name": "",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "ivanreese",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "edited": {
      "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
