  {
    "client_msg_id": "03ff710d-679b-409b-af7b-dc4e6d7974a5",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Yea right now we basically have capabilities to do really nice digital articles, and some small bits and pieces of interactivity. We plan on expanding that. Our 3 word vision is \"apps for everyone\". It's a big vision but that's where we want to go.\n\nWe're also unsure about drawing a parallel with Flash honestly. I guess I've been thinking lately that although Flash had a bad rep at the end, IMO it definitely had more of that apps for everyone mantra than where we're at today on the web. It ushered in a massive wave of amateur and professional coders making really rich applications.",
    "user": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "ts": "1568356625.185200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "2cbc18c8ae90",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-09-12/760980944038_2cbc18c8ae90630cd996_72.png",
      "first_name": "",
      "real_name": "Parris",
      "display_name": "Parris",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "parris",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1568330809.182600",
    "parent_user_id": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "channel_name": "introduce-yourself",
    "channel_id": "CC2JRGVLK"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "b32613d0-a253-425f-b441-ccb5dade4176",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "A lot of the Flash bad reputation was nasty propaganda from Adobe hating companies, which included almost everyone. Adobe makes great stuff, but so many other companies feared it. Microsoft and Apple both did battle with Adobe's creativity tools, and often came up on the losing end. MS spent untold hundreds of millions building clones of Flash/Shockwave (their Silverlight), and tried to build publishing tools, etc., and Apple also had a fantasy that their Pages would somehow hold up against InDesign. MS and Apple teamed up to make TrueType to counter Adobe's Type 1 font format which they didn't want to pay for. Lots of rivalries between these companies, and lots of FUD (fear uncertainty and doubt) press releases sponsored by the negative-evangelical arms of those firms. Not many people  acknowledge the existence of those kinds of PR staffers, but they do exist.  I am personally sick of people pretending that everyone in the valley is playing sports like a proper english gentleman. There are tons of dirty tricks, and the bigger the company the dirtier they get IMHO. Who can forget Intel paying companies huge bonuses if they ship only 100% intel parts. that is so purely anticompetitive, they should have put intel CEO in jail.",
    "user": "UEQ6M68H0",
    "ts": "1568533013.001800",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
      "avatar_hash": "326328f75c3f",
      "image_72": "https://avatars.slack-edge.com/2019-02-05/542651515888_326328f75c3f2a08544c_72.jpg",
      "first_name": "Edward",
      "real_name": "Edward de Jong",
      "display_name": "Edward de Jong / Beads Project",
      "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
      "name": "magicmouse94937",
      "is_restricted": false,
      "is_ultra_restricted": false
    },
    "thread_ts": "1568330809.182600",
    "parent_user_id": "UMXUZ97LJ",
    "channel_name": "introduce-yourself",
    "channel_id": "CC2JRGVLK"
  },
  {
    "client_msg_id": "488898ef-c461-402d-87ee-3e5486642fa1",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "And Saint Jobs had a whole layer of lawyer/VP's who do nothing but try and suppress bad stories, and take revenge on people who cross them. I never worked with Jobs, but i remember apple going to great lengths to try and find leverage on me for just a simple complaint.",
    "user": "UEQ6M68H0",
    "ts": "1568533135.002000",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
